From f5ac6f155131522a9098b72b2d9ba6f7ba67dad5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 10:30:45 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(persistence): add version guards to all stores,
 reset-to-seed action (Phase 5)

- ingestionStore.ts, workflowStore.ts, auditStore.ts: added version: 1
  + migrate guards matching coreStore.ts's existing pattern -- these
  three were the only ones missing it, meaning a future shape change
  to any of them would have silently rehydrated an incompatible
  persisted state instead of cleanly resetting.
- src/lib/resetSeedData.ts: resetToSeedData() clears all 4
  localStorage keys and reloads; clearPersistedStores() is the same
  without the reload, for use before the app has rendered.
- SystemTelemetry.tsx: added a 'Reset to Seed Data' button with an
  explicit confirm step (destructive -- wipes real session edits).
  Chose this page since it's already the closest thing to a system
  diagnostics view; there's no dedicated settings page yet.
- main.tsx: added optional VITE_RESET_ON_LOAD env flag, off by
  default, for CI/demo runs that need to always start from pristine
  mock data rather than whatever localStorage has from a previous run.

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, full vitest suite green (85 files /
401 tests, 0 regressions).
